'''Thunder''' is a character from the tactical SRPG ES game '''[[Girls' Frontline]]''' developed by MicaTeam, published by Digital Sky, and its derivatives. She joined the struggle on February 8, 2018.

== Historical basis ==
The Thunder .50 BMG is designed and manufactured by Utah-based firm Triple Action LLC with the aims to create a pistol capable of firing .50 BMG rounds. It is first shown to the public at the SHOT Show in Las Vegas in 2004. Finalized models have a weight of 12 lbs (5.44 kg), a length of 16.9 in (429.26mm) and a barrel length of 13.2 in (335.28mm), and are loaded from the rear, housing a single cartridge. The weapon needs to be manually unlocked and its case extracted before loading a new round and locking the weapon for the next shot.

The .50BMG boasts a high kinetic energy, making the muzzle energy of the Thunder reach 15,500 J. To mitigate the strong recoil caused by .50 rounds, the weapon is equipped with a high-efficiency muzzle brake capable of relieving 20% to 25% of the recoil<ref>http://best-top10.ru/samye-moshhnye-pistolety-v-mire.html</ref><ref>https://www.drive2.ru/b/482658117876711582/</ref> and a nitrogen recoil-absorption mechanism<ref>http://topnewsanimals.info/2018/02/06/50-bmg-pistol-kiss-your-wrists-goodbye/</ref>. Despite the incorporation of such mechanisms, the recoil from the pistol is still strong enough to rival that of a 7.62mm NATO-chambering rifle.

===Specifications===
*Caliber: 12.7mm (.50 in)
*Cartridge: .50 BMG (12.7×99mm NATO)
*Empty weight: 5.44 kg (12 lbs)
*Overall length: 429.26 mm (16.9 in)
*Barrel length: 335.28 mm (13.2 in)
*Feed system: Single-shot, closed-chamber
*Action: Side-swung breech with separate cocking lever and extractor
*Trigger pull: 0.454-5.443 kgf (1-12 lbf)

