Her illustrator, NIN, released the setting drafts for Thunder on June 6, 2018, and provided large amounts of text to describe her daughter.

{{Cquote|''Was instantly cool'd when looking for information on this gun, the super-large caliber different from other pistols, the hairdryer-ish look, the unsatisfactory sales, the final work of a speedily-collapsing R&D company, without anything not even efficiency or prospect, a gun made solely for romance. Set this kid's image early on.''

''Clothing is quite ordinary suit-dress plus a coat, and pantyhoses and armpads. Was it not for someone attracted by black silk, I believe this would be a combination with decent defense. Dressed as a shy kid, with a small constrast by the ribbon on her leg. The entire design is simple, putting most of the emphasis on the doll and the color of the clothing. A white swan in the clothes of a black swan, hoped to give off some hidden morals.''

''The black swan mentioned here is the one referring to an event, but borrowed the outline of living beings, which included the sense of a crow. The camouflage is placed on the inside of the clothes, meant for herself, not to forget the cruelty and darkness of the world. Once the coat is buttoned up, the ribbon on the leg will be hidden as well. In the shadow, not standing out means not to be chosen, living silently in a shell.''}}

